
[1]low-spirited

   LOW-SPIR'ITED, a. Not having animation and courage; dejected;
   depressed; not lively or sprightly. Losses of property often render men
   low-spirited. Excessive severity breaks the mind, and renders the child
   or pupil low-spirited.
